The paper discusses a comparative study of pre-print papers and their final published counterparts in the field of science, technology, and medicine. This study involves analyzing the text contents of the papers and detecting and quantifying differences using standard similarity measures. This topic is relevant to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.CY (Computers and Society), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). However, given the focus on scholarly communications and academic publishing, cs.DL and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories.
